description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Northern Lincolnshire and Goole NHS Foundation Trust are now recruiting nursing students who are due to qualify in 2021. You will be invited to a Virtual Nursing Recruitment Open Day where you’ll have the opportunity to meet some of our teams and be interviewed for a position.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Those who attend the open day will gain insight into what it’s like working at the Trust which runs the hospitals in Scunthorpe, Grimsby and Goole, as well as community services in North Lincolnshire.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For those who have not worked in the Trust before there will be a virtual tour of the hospitals and services so you can explore your potential new workplace.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will have the opportunity to meet some of the Senior Nursing team and also hear the experiences of our current newly qualified nurses.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have opportunities at Grimsby, Scunthorpe and Goole hospitals within all specialties. There are also opportunities to join our Community Nursing Teams in North Lincolnshire.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you’d like to find out more about the a Virtual Nursing Recruitment Open Day, please &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;email Deputy Chief Nurse, Jenny Hinchliffe, on &lt;/span&gt;jennifer.hinchliffe1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; or Recruitment Team Leader, Laura Anderson, on &lt;/span&gt;laura.anderson6@nhs.net&lt;span&gt; .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
